title: Protect your land and property from fraud

heading_context: Protect your land and property from fraud
chunks.html_content: You can take steps to protect your property from being fraudulently sold or mortgaged.
chunks.plain_content:
Protect your land and property from fraud
You can take steps to protect your property from being fraudulently sold or mortgaged.

heading_context: Protect your land and property from fraud
chunks.plain_content:
Protect your land and property from fraud
This guide is also available in Welsh (Cymraeg).

heading_context: Protect your land and property from fraud
chunks.html_content:
Youre more at risk if:

  • your identitys been stolen
  • you rent out your property
  • you live overseas
  • the propertys empty
  • the property is not mortgaged
  • the property is not registered with HM Land Registry

Your property will be registered if you bought it or mortgaged it since 1998 - check the register if youre unsure.

heading_context: Protect your land and property from fraud
chunks.html_content: You must tell HM Land Registry if information in the register is incorrect, for example if you change your contact address.
chunks.plain_content:
Protect your land and property from fraud
You must tell HM Land Registry if information in the register is incorrect, for example if you change your contact address.

heading_context: Protect your land and property from fraud
Track changes to the register
chunks.html_content:
You can track changes to the register or put a restriction on your title if you think youre at risk.

You can sign up to get property alerts if someone applies to change the register of your property, for example if someone tries to use your property for a mortgage.

This will not automatically block any changes to the register but will alert you when something changes so that you can take action.

You can get alerts for up to 10 properties - theres no fee.

heading_context: Protect your land and property from fraud
Put a restriction on your title
Business owners
chunks.html_content:
You can stop HM Land Registry registering a sale or mortgage on your property unless a conveyancer or solicitor certifies the application was made by you.

Your conveyancer or solicitor may charge you for providing a certificate if one is required by a restriction on your property.

Fill in a request for a restriction if youre a company owning property.

Send your application to the address on the form - theres no fee.

Send completed forms to the HM Land Registry Citizen Centre.
